.TH "efi_exit_boot_services" 9 "efi_exit_boot_services" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_exit_boot_services \- Exit boot services
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "efi_status_t" efi_exit_boot_services
.BI "(void *handle "  ","
.BI "struct efi_boot_memmap *map "  ","
.BI "void *priv "  ","
.BI "efi_exit_boot_map_processing priv_func "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
handle of the exiting image
.IP "map" 12
pointer to receive the memory map
.IP "priv" 12
argument to be passed to \fIpriv_func\fP
.IP "priv_func" 12
function to process the memory map before exiting boot services
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Handle calling ExitBootServices according to the requirements set out by the
spec.  Obtains the current memory map, and returns that info after calling
ExitBootServices.  The client must specify a function to perform any
processing of the memory map data prior to ExitBootServices.  A client
specific structure may be passed to the function via priv.  The client
function may be called multiple times.
.SH "RETURN"
status code
